lysis\\resource-map.json`)\n193: - `android-analysis/screen-map.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\screen-map.json`)\n194: - `android-analysis/view-bindings.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\view-bindings.json`)\n195: - `android-analysis/layout-tree.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\layout-tree.json`)\n196: - `android-analysis/drawable-semantics.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\drawable-semantics.json`)\n197: - `android-analysis/adapter-map.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\adapter-map.json`)\n198: - `android-analysis/data-schema.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\data-schema.json`)\n199: - `android-analysis/crud-slices.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\crud-slices.json`)\n200: - `android-analysis/backend-api-usage.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\backend-api-usage.json`)\n201: - `android-analysis/room-schema.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\room-schema.json`)\n202: - `android-analysis/retrofit-endpoints.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\retrofit-endpoints.json`)\n203: - `android-analysis/sqlite-schema.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\sqlite-schema.json`)\n204: - `android-analysis/preferences-map.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\preferences-map.json`)\n205: - `android-analysis/refresh-chains.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\refresh-chains.json`)\n206: - `android-analysis/aggregate-semantics.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\aggregate-semantics.json`)\n207: - `android-analysis/method-summaries.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\method-summaries.json`)\n208: - `android-analysis/data-flow-gaps.json`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\data-flow-gaps.json`)\n209: - `android-analysis/behavior-spec.md`: present (`D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\android-analysis\\behavior-spec.md`)\n210: \n211: If an input is missing, do not invent its contents. Fall back to source inspection only for the evidence needed by the current task, and report the gap.\n212: \n213: Treat Kotlin source, Gradle metadata, Compose state, ViewModel/repository flow, resources, navigation, and user-visible refresh behavior as behavior evidence. Do not translate only UI skeletons; preserve search, filtering, CRUD, persistence, selection, dialogs, bottom bars, and immediate UI update semantics.\n214: \n215: Coverage reports are a baseline for reducing functional gaps and unexplained code-scale gaps. Do not mechanically match source LoC. Instead, map current-scope critical/high source features, resources, tests, and platform integrations to target implementation, supplemental tests, platform replacement, or explicit deferred items. `source-coverage-matrix.json` is the feature status record and `platform-capability-check.json` is the target platform capability status record: use both during planning and update them during phase/repair work. The main planning session should prioritize valid `plan.md` and `plan.json`; row-level `plannedPhase` backfill may be applied by a separate post-planning records-only session after the plan contract passes. Use language-specific static analysis outputs to refine the matrix when present. If static analysis reveals a source feature missing from the matrix template, add a matrix entry with source evidence. Critical/high `implemented` entries need specific evidence: do not bulk-promote many rows with the same notes/tests/endpoints, do not rely only on root views, shell views, state classes, whole files, or grouped endpoint lists, and do not cite target tests as strong evidence unless the notes record a successful target test compile/run command. For every closed critical/high feature, record `sourceBehavior`, `targetBehavior`, `parityLevel`, and `verificationEvidence` in `source-coverage-matrix.json`; `implemented` should use `parityLevel: equivalent`, `implemented-simplified` should use `parityLevel: simplified`, and `platform-replaced` should use `parityLevel: platform-replaced`. `verification-results.json/md` is generated evidence from build/test/manual reports, but a build pass alone is not per-feature behavior verification. Critical/high `implemented-simplified` is exceptional: record what was simplified, why user-visible behavior remains acceptable, target endpoints or tests, and source/platform evidence. Critical/high deferred feat... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n216: \n217: For this workflow, direct target API evidence means the capability is callable\n218: from the HarmonyOS Cangjie target. ArkTS `.d.ts` declarations, JS APIs, native C\n219: headers/libraries, or generic HarmonyOS capability docs are useful discovery\n220: evidence, but they are not direct Cangjie evidence by themselves. If only\n221: ArkTS/native bindings are found, record the missing Cangjie binding as a\n222: concrete blocker with fallback/deferred behavior unless a Cangjie wrapper, FFI,\n223: or bridge is already part of the target architecture or explicitly planned and\n224: verified with target endpoints plus build evidence. Do not introduce the first\n225: ArkTS/JS/native bridge merely to close coverage or capability rows, and do not\n226: mark a capability `verified-direct` or upgrade a feature to equivalent solely\n227: from ArkTS/native evidence.\n228: \n229: When checking current SDK availability, search pure Cangjie declarations first:\n230: `$HOME/.cangjie-sdk/**/cangjie/api/modules` for `.cj.d` files and\n231: `$HOME/.cangjie-sdk/**/cangjie/api/lib` for matching `.cjo` libraries. Treat\n232: DevEco ETS/JS/native SDK files as secondary discovery evidence unless a\n233: Cangjie-callable binding is found or already belongs to the target architecture.\n234: \n235: Static analysis is implementation evidence, not just matrix evidence. Use it during planning to decide phase boundaries, source evidence, files/assets/dependencies, state/data flow, platform replacement points, and test strategy. Use it during phase work to locate source behavior and preserve view/page bindings, event handlers, CRUD/persistence/API paths, refresh chains, schemas, resources, tests, and user-visible side effects. Use it during build or coverage repair to avoid deleting source-covered behavior merely to satisfy the compiler. When static analysis is incomplete or conflicts with source code, inspect the minimal relevant source files and follow the source code.\n236: \n237: Deferred is a last resort, not a planning shortcut. Do not mark features deferred merely because they are large, tedious, or inconvenient for compilation. Prefer faithful implementation; if exact parity is impossible, use the closest working implementation that preserves user-visible behavior and records the simplification reason; if platform capability differs, use a real HarmonyOS/Cangjie replacement. Use fallback or deferred only when a concrete blocker remains, such as unavailable HarmonyOS/Cangjie SDK capability, external service credentials, hardware/device dependency, legal/security constraint, or human product decision. Avoid bulk-deferred entries with repeated generic reasons.\n238: \n239: For ArkTS projects, prefer `arkts-analysis/compiler-summary.json`, `arkts-analysis/compiler-planning-note.md`, and phase-relevant compiler sidecars such as `compiler/behavior-spec.md`, `compiler/refresh-chains.json`, `compiler/method-summaries.json`, and `compiler/artifacts/cangjie-mapping-hints.json` before opening the full `arkts-analysis/compiler/analysis.json`.\n240: \n241: ## Static Analysis Limits\n242: \n243: Generated static analysis inputs are aids, not complete truth. They may miss dynamic dispatch, reflection, generated code, callback wiring, resource indirection, build-variant behavior, or platform-specific side effects. Do not rely only on static analysis when source behavior is unclear or when coverage reports indicate possible omissions. Inspect the minimal relevant source files and resources before deciding to simplify, replace, or defer behavior. For Kotlin projects, pay particular attention to Compose state, remembered state, ViewModel/repository flow, coroutine side effects, navigation arguments, and resource bindings that may be missing or only partially summarized.\n244: \n245: ## Target Architecture Organization\n246: \n247: Use the source project structure as a responsibility guide, then adapt it to\n248: idiomatic HarmonyOS Cangjie modules. Do not mechanically mirror Android\n249: Activity, Fragment, Adapter, BroadcastReceiver, ContentProvider, or XML layout\n250: boundaries, but also do not collapse unrelated domain behavior into broad files\n\n(Showing lines 1-250 of 450. Use offset=251 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Android Kotlin to HarmonyOS Cangjie Translation Plan\n\n## Goal\n\nTranslate the Android Kotlin project in `D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike` into a HarmonyOS Cangjie project rooted at `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`, preserving main features, screen flow, resources, state changes, data behavior, tests, and user-visible side effects while adapting implementation to HarmonyOS Cangjie patterns.\n\n## Paths\n\n- App name: `Foodike`\n- Source kind: `kotlin`\n- Translation workspace: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike`\n- Workspace standing instructions: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\AGENTS.md`\n- Source project: `D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike`\n- Target HarmonyOS Cangjie project: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n- Translation inputs: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs`\n- Translation records: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-records`\n- Agent protocol: `D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\docs\\android-kotlin-to-cangjie-agent-protocol.md`\n- HarmonyOS Cangjie checklist: `D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md`\n\n## Role Split","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"task-planning.md","time":{"start":1782536313564,"end":1782536313572}},"id":"prt_f07719ad1001VtUcM0MHaoYhjJ","sessionID":"ses_0f88ea0d8ffeABtVVgM5lrUMXi","messageID":"msg_f07717c44001ByJXQNiH352dEd"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782536313576,"sessionID":"ses_0f88ea0d8ffeABtVVgM5lrUMXi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_p0JjdPAJss6yUw1RRKc2Uc4b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\plan.json","limit":250,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\plan.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"files\": [\n3:     {\n4:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj\",\n5:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n6:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/MainActivity.kt\",\n7:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Navigation.kt\"\n8:       ],\n9:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n10:         \"bootstrap page shell\",\n11:         \"root route composition\"\n12:       ],\n13:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n14:         \"Keep this file as a shell that delegates to feature modules.\",\n15:         \"Do not absorb repository or screen-specific logic here.\"\n16:       ]\n17:     },\n18:     {\n19:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj\",\n20:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n21:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Navigation.kt\",\n22:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Screen.kt\"\n23:       ],\n24:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n25:         \"route ids\",\n26:         \"navigation helpers\",\n27:         \"bottom shell visibility rules\"\n28:       ],\n29:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n30:         \"Preserve onboarding/login/home/history/cart/profile/detail routes.\",\n31:         \"Preserve home/history bottom bar plus cart action visibility semantics.\"\n32:       ]\n33:     },\n34:     {\n35:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/startup\",\n36:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n37:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/common/SplashViewModel.kt\",\n38:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/MainActivity.kt\"\n39:       ],\n40:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n41:         \"startup state store\",\n42:         \"start destination resolver\"\n43:       ],\n44:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n45:         \"Startup logic should read persisted session state and decide onboarding vs home before normal route rendering.\"\n46:       ]\n47:     },\n48:     {\n49:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session\",\n50:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n51:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/repository/LoginRepositoryImpl.kt\",\n52:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/repository/UserDataRepositoryImpl.kt\",\n53:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/domain/repository/LoginRepository.kt\",\n54:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/domain/repository/UserDataRepository.kt\"\n55:       ],\n56:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n57:         \"session persistence service\",\n58:         \"selected restaurant store\",\n59:         \"liked restaurant stream\",\n60:         \"cart item stream\"\n61:       ],\n62:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n63:         \"Keep persistent login state separate from fake catalogue content.\",\n64:         \"Expose stream-like update surfaces so UI refresh remains immediate after mutations.\"\n65:       ]\n66:     },\n67:     {\n68:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/content\",\n69:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n70:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/data_source/FakeData.kt\",\n71:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/repository/HomeRepositoryImpl.kt\"\n72:       ],\n73:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n74:         \"fake catalogue data\",\n75:         \"ads/food/restaurant repository implementations\",\n76:         \"search and lookup helpers\"\n77:       ],\n78:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n79:         \"Split catalog, restaurant, and helper logic into focused files rather than one giant data source translation.\"\n80:       ]\n81:     },\n82:     {\n83:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/onboarding\",\n84:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n85:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/onboarding/OnBoarding.kt\",\n86:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/onboarding/components/OnboardingPage.kt\",\n87:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/onboarding/util/OnBoardingItem.kt\"\n88:       ],\n89:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n90:         \"onboarding page\",\n91:         \"pager state\",\n92:         \"page item builder\"\n93:       ],\n94:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n95:         \"Preserve onboarding sequencing and transition into login.\"\n96:       ]\n97:     },\n98:     {\n99:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login\",\n100:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n101:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/LoginScreen.kt\",\n102:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/LoginViewModel.kt\",\n103:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/components/FoodikeTextField.kt\"\n104:       ],\n105:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n106:         \"login page\",\n107:         \"login reducer/store\",\n108:         \"text field widget\"\n109:       ],\n110:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n111:         \"Preserve hard-coded credential check, snackbar error, and successful navigation to home after session toggle.\"\n112:       ]\n113:     },\n114:     {\n115:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/home\",\n116:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n117:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/home/HomeScreen.kt\",\n118:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/home/HomeViewModel.kt\",\n119:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/home/HomeScreenState.kt\",\n120:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/home/components/*.kt\",\n121:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/components/SearchBar.kt\",\n122:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/components/RestaurantCard.kt\"\n123:       ],\n124:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n125:         \"home page\",\n126:         \"home state store\",\n127:         \"home widgets\",\n128:         \"search/filter helpers\"\n129:       ],\n130:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n131:         \"Preserve section order, conditional favourites block, and restaurant selection path into detail state.\"\n132:       ]\n133:     },\n134:     {\n135:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/history\",\n136:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n137:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/history/History.kt\",\n138:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/history/HistoryViewModel.kt\",\n139:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/history/components/*.kt\"\n140:       ],\n141:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n142:         \"history page\",\n143:         \"liked restaurants state store\",\n144:         \"tab content widgets\"\n145:       ],\n146:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n147:         \"Preserve tabs plus liked restaurant selection into detail route.\"\n148:       ]\n149:     },\n150:     {\n151:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/detail\",\n152:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n153:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/details/RestaurantDetail.kt\",\n154:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/details/RestaurantDetailViewModel.kt\",\n155:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/details/DetailScreenState.kt\",\n156:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/details/components/*.kt\"\n157:       ],\n158:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n159:         \"detail page\",\n160:         \"detail state store\",\n161:         \"menu grouping helpers\",\n162:         \"detail widgets\"\n163:       ],\n164:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n165:         \"Preserve expandable recommended, non-veg, and veg sections and cart action visibility when total count is non-zero.\"\n166:       ]\n167:     },\n168:     {\n169:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/cart\",\n170:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n171:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/cart/Cart.kt\",\n172:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/cart/CartViewModel.kt\",\n173:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/cart/CartState.kt\",\n174:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/cart/components/*.kt\"\n175:       ],\n176:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n177:         \"cart page\",\n178:         \"cart state store\",\n179:         \"cart summary widgets\"\n180:       ],\n181:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n182:         \"Keep item filtering, coupon, delivery, and bill sections modular; do not fold them into the root page file.\"\n183:       ]\n184:     },\n185:     {\n186:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/profile\",\n187:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n188:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/profile/Profile.kt\",\n189:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/profile/ProfileViewModel.kt\",\n190:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/profile/components/ProfileCard.kt\"\n191:       ],\n192:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n193:         \"profile page\",\n194:         \"logout action handler\",\n195:         \"profile option widgets\"\n196:       ],\n197:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n198:         \"Preserve logout to onboarding and keep current placeholder cards explicit rather than silently omitted.\"\n199:       ]\n200:     },\n201:     {\n202:       \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/common/foodike_resources.cj\",\n203:       \"sourceReferences\": [\n204:         \"app/src/main/res/values/strings.xml\",\n205:         \"app/src/main/res/values/colors.xml\",\n206:         \"app/src/main/res/values/themes.xml\"\n207:       ],\n208:       \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n209:         \"resource lookup helpers\",\n210:         \"string and color mapping\"\n211:       ],\n212:       \"translationGuidelines\": [\n213:         \"Avoid hard-coded English labels for migrated UI text.\"\n214:       ]\n215:     }\n216:   ],\n217:   \"assets\": [\n218:     {\n219:       \"assetType\": \"strings\",\n220:       \"sourcePaths\": [\n221:         \"app/src/main/res/values/strings.xml\"\n222:       ],\n223:       \"targetPaths\": [\n224:         \"entry/src/main/resources/base/element/string.json\",\n225:         \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/common/foodike_resources.cj\"\n226:       ],\n227:       \"rules\": [\n228:         \"Migrate all user-visible source strings, especially onboarding, login, navigation, cart, detail, profile, and placeholder labels.\",\n229:         \"Keep resource ids stable enough for later matrix evidence and tests.\"\n230:       ]\n231:     },\n232:     {\n233:       \"assetType\": \"colors-and-theme\",\n234:       \"sourcePaths\": [\n235:         \"app/src/main/res/values/colors.xml\",\n236:         \"app/src/main/res/values/themes.xml\",\n237:         \"app/src/main/res/values/ic_launcher_background.xml\"\n238:       ],\n239:       \"targetPaths\": [\n240:         \"entry/src/main/resources/base/element/color.json\"\n241:       ],\n242:       \"rules\": [\n243:         \"Carry over primary/neutral accents that drive onboarding, top bars, and cards.\",\n244:         \"Map status/navigation bar styling intent into HarmonyOS page/theme composition where available.\"\n245:       ]\n246:     },\n247:     {\n248:       \"assetType\": \"drawables-and-images\",\n249:       \"sourcePaths\": [\n250:         \"app/src/main/res/drawable\",\n\n(Showing lines 1-250 of 1265. Use offset=251 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj\",\n      \"sourceReferences\": [\n        \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/MainActivity.kt\",\n        \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Navigation.kt\"\n      ],\n      \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n        \"bootstrap page shell\",\n        \"root route composition\"\n      ],\n      \"translationGuidelines\": [\n        \"Keep this file as a shell that delegates to feature modules.\",\n        \"Do not absorb repository or screen-specific logic here.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj\",\n      \"sourceReferences\": [","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"plan.json","time":{"start":1782536313571,"end":1782536313575}},"id":"prt_f07719adf001wMOFDXvISEjcRC","sessionID":"ses_0f88ea0d8ffeABtVVgM5lrUMXi","messageID":"msg_f07717c44001ByJXQNiH352dEd"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782536313727,"sessionID":"ses_0f88ea0d8ffeABtVVgM5lrUMXi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_V854DjLhKNUqjuXlx3nLBoId","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md","limit":250,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # HarmonyOS Cangjie Translation Checklist\n2: \n3: 面向 Android Java app 迁移到 HarmonyOS Cangjie 的阶段性检查表。它来自 Spendee 案例记录和后续构建修复经验，目标是在每个 `opencode-cj` phase 结束时先抓住高频编译/宏展开问题，再进入下一阶段。\n4: \n5: ## 使用时机\n6: \n7: 1. 每个翻译 phase 开始前，把本 phase 可能触及的条目加入 `opencode-cj` prompt。\n8: 2. 每个 phase 结束后，先运行完整构建门禁：\n9: \n10:    `<python>` 表示当前 Python 解释器：macOS/Linux 可用 `python3`，Windows 可用 `py -3` 或 `python`。\n11: \n12:    ```bash\n13:    <python> scripts/shared/reports/build_hap_report.py \\\n14:      --workspace-root <translation-workspace> \\\n15:      --target-project <target-project> \\\n16:      --phase <phase-name>\n17:    ```\n18: \n19: 3. 如果报告失败，把 `build-reports/<phase-name>/build-report.md` 和首个 blocker 交给 `opencode-cj` 修复当前 phase，不要先开启下一阶段。\n20: 4. 构建通过后，再进入运行时 smoke 或行为验证。\n21: \n22: ## 资源和字符串边界\n23: \n24: - 不要把 `@r(...)` / `AppResource` 直接当作普通 `String`。\n25: - UI prop 如果可能接收资源字符串，优先使用 `ResourceStr`，或在边界处做 SDK 支持的显式转换。\n26: - 不要对 `ResourceStr` 调用普通字符串方法，例如 `isEmpty()`；需要空态时使用独立 `Bool` 状态。\n27: - 迁移 Android `setText(...)` 时，确认 HarmonyOS 端有明确的状态赋值或可观察数据源驱动文本刷新。\n28: - 每次资源迁移后，检查 `string.json`、media 资源和实际 UI 引用，避免保留旧 placeholder key 或缺失 AppScope/entry 双层资源。\n29: \n30: ## Option 和控制流\n31: \n32: - 不要生成 Java/Kotlin 风格的 `Option.get()`。\n33: - 非 UI helper 中使用 `match`、显式 `case Some(...)` / `case None`，或当前 SDK 支持的安全访问 API。\n34: - UI 构建逻辑中避免直接让 `match` 分支裸露生成不兼容的 component 形态；需要时拆成命名 `@Builder`。\n35: - 启动/依赖注入状态建议拆成明确的 `Bool`、错误资源、服务 option 解包 helper，减少 `@Component` 宏失败面。\n36: \n37: ## 包结构和导入\n38: \n39: - 避免 root package 与 `pages` / `routing` 之间出现环形依赖。公共 route 类型优先放在 `routing` 或独立 models/helpers 包。\n40: - UI 文件中避免宽泛 `std.collection.*` 导入；它可能和 ArkUI 组件名冲突，例如 `Stack`。\n41: - 需要集合类型时优先显式导入或限定命名。\n42: - helper 类型如果会通过 public `@Component` 生成构造器暴露，确认类型本身也是必要的 public 可见性。\n43: - 不要把临时 template/cache 文件当成迁移输入；`.cache`、build output 和 diagnostic log 只作为诊断证据。\n44: \n45: ## ArkUI Component 和 Builder\n46: \n47: - `@BuilderParam` 优先传入命名 `@Builder` 方法，不要依赖未验证的 inline closure 或 trailing component block。\n48: - 自定义容器组件要按当前 SDK 支持的构造器/slot 形态实现，不能照搬 ArkTS 示例。\n49: - 校验 ArkUI named arguments 和 modifiers 来自当前 Cangjie HarmonyOS SDK 文档，而不是只参考 ArkTS。\n50: - 对 `@Component` macro 失败，先缩小到入口组件状态、构造器 public 类型、资源字符串类型和 `@Publish` 字段类型这四类高频根因。\n51: - 组件内部紧密相关的 owner state 文本可直接在 owning page builder 中渲染，避免子组件 prop 复用导致同会话文本不刷新。\n52: \n53: ## 状态和可观察集合\n54: \n55: - 路由和跨页面状态模型使用 SDK 支持的 `@Observed`、`@Publish` 和明确字段类型。\n56: - 需要列表变化驱动 UI 时，使用 `ObservedArrayList` 等 SDK 支持的数据源，并给 `ForEach` 提供稳定 key。\n57: - 不要假设 `ObservedArrayList` 是普通 iterator；辅助逻辑中用下标访问或 SDK 支持方法。\n58: - 跨组件变化的 prop 需要 `@Prop` / `@Link` / `@Watch` 等明确同步链路。\n59: - 对 primitive totals、余额、计数等关键展示值，保存/编辑/删除成功后优先执行明确赋值，避免只依赖持久化回读触发 UI。\n60: \n61: ## 测试迁移和验证\n62: \n63: - 源项目已有测试时，当前 phase 相关测试应迁移或改写为目标侧测试，验证翻译后的业务、数据、状态、资源或刷新行为。\n64: - 源项目没有测试时，应为核心可测试逻辑补充适量测试；源测试过少时，应优先补高风险行为测试。\n65: - 如果当前 SDK/模板不支持某类自动化测试，应保持代码可测试，并记录 deferred validation、替代验证方法和后续完成路径。\n66: - 不要为了通过构建直接删除、禁用或弱化已迁移/生成的测试；应修实现、修测试集成，或明确记录当前阶段测试限制。\n67: \n68: ## 构建配置和工具链\n69: \n70: - 完整 HAP 构建必须使用 DevEco Cangjie plugin 管理的 full SDK，例如 `~/.cangjie-sdk/<version>/cangjie`；standalone `~/.local/cangjie` 只能代表轻量 `cjc` / `cjpm` 可用。\n71: - 缺少 full SDK 时，应先安装/启用 DevEco Studio Cangjie plugin，再继续 full build gate。\n72: - 每阶段记录构建命令、失败阶段、首个 blocker 和已解决 blocker。\n73: - 常见阶段含义：\n74:   - `ohpm install`：依赖、registry、模板测试依赖或 oh-package 问题。\n75:   - `SyncCangjieResource`：资源生成、配置 schema、Cangjie build support 注入问题。\n76:   - `CompileCangjie`：Cangjie 语法、宏展开、包依赖、ArkUI API 问题。\n77:   - `PackageHap`：资源/loader/package 产物问题。\n78:   - `SignHap`：签名配置问题；未签名 debug HAP 通常可能只是 warning。\n79: - full build 通过前，不要把 standalone `cjpm check` 失败简单等同于 HAP 构建失败；两者依赖来源不同。\n80: \n81: ## opencode-cj 修复交接\n82: \n83: - `apply_patch` 失败后必须 read-back，因为失败可能部分落盘。\n84: - `L.map is not a function`、`apply_patch verification failed`、`Failed to read file to update` 要分开记录。\n85: - 长 phase 被打断或恢复时，先让 `opencode-cj` 检查文件系统当前状态，再继续，不要重复生成同名组件或服务。\n86: - 构建 blocker prompt 应包含：\n87:   - 当前 phase 名称。\n88:   - `build-report.md` 路径。\n89:   - 失败阶段。\n90:   - 首个 blocker message 和 location。\n91:   - 只修当前 phase blocker 的约束。\n92: \n93: ## Phase Gate 验收\n94: \n95: - `build_hap_report.py` 的 Markdown/JSON 报告存在。\n96: - 报告包含 command、result、failed stage、first blocker、warnings、HAP artifacts。\n97: - 如果失败，已有 `opencode-build-blocker-prompt.txt` 可直接交给 `opencode-cj`。\n98: - 如果成功，报告记录 full build gate 通过，且可把本 phase 的已知编译 blocker 标为 resolved。\n99: - 下一 phase 只能在构建通过，或用户明确批准带 blocker 继续时开始。\n100: \n101: ## Spendee 证据映射\n102: \n103: - `@r(...)` / `ResourceStr` 误用导致重复 generic inference 和 macro blocker。\n104: - `Option.get()` 在当前 SDK 下不可用，入口和服务解包需改为显式 `match`。\n105: - root/pages/routing 包循环会阻断 `CompileCangjie`。\n106: - UI 文件中的 `std.collection.*` 与 ArkUI `Stack` 名称冲突。\n107: - `@BuilderParam` 命名 builder 比 inline closure 更稳定。\n108: - `ObservedArrayList` 不能按普通 `for-in` 假设处理。\n109: - 同会话 finance totals 刷新最终需要 owner state、显式赋值和可观察列表配合，构建通过不能替代运行时刷新验证。\n110: - 如果 full SDK 在 Phase 1 就接入，许多 Cangjie/ArkUI 编译问题可以在引入当 phase 就暴露，而不是累积到最终构建。\n\n(End of file - total 110 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# HarmonyOS Cangjie Translation Checklist\n\n面向 Android Java app 迁移到 HarmonyOS Cangjie 的阶段性检查表。它来自 Spendee 案例记录和后续构建修复经验，目标是在每个 `opencode-cj` phase 结束时先抓住高频编译/宏展开问题，再进入下一阶段。\n\n## 使用时机\n\n1. 每个翻译 phase 开始前，把本 phase 可能触及的条目加入 `opencode-cj` prompt。\n2. 每个 phase 结束后，先运行完整构建门禁：\n\n   `<python>` 表示当前 Python 解释器：macOS/Linux 可用 `python3`，Windows 可用 `py -3` 或 `python`。\n\n   ```bash\n   <python> scripts/shared/reports/build_hap_report.py \\\n     --workspace-root <translation-workspace> \\\n     --target-project <target-project> \\\n     --phase <phase-name>\n   ```\n\n3. 如果报告失败，把 `build-reports/<phase-name>/build-report.md` 和首个 blocker 交给 `opencode-cj` 修复当前 phase，不要先开启下一阶段。\n4. 构建通过后，再进入运行时 smoke 或行为验证。","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"..\\..\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md","time":{"start":1782536313722,"end":1782536313727}},"id":"prt_f07719b77001Tc0aZnarsU4k73","sessionID":"ses_0f88ea0d8ffeABtVVgM5lrUMXi","messageID":"msg_f07717c44001ByJXQNiH352dEd"}}
